<requirements>
- Content type: {{ ctx.slot_type }}
- Word count: {{ type_cfg.min_words }}-{{ type_cfg.max_words }} words
- Language: Ukrainian
- MUST include source URLs for every factual claim
- Slug: latin lowercase with hyphens, descriptive, SEO-friendly
- Tags: Ukrainian topic tags relevant to the article
- Hashtags: combine city hashtags (#Lisbon, #Porto, etc.) with topic hashtags (#News, #Immigration, etc.)
- Image prompt: describe a comic-style illustration for this article (in English, for DALL-E)
  - Style: colorful comic book illustration, clean lines, warm palette
  - Include relevant Portuguese visual elements (tiles, sardines, tram, etc.)
  - NO text in the image
  - NO real people or politicians
- CONTEXT FOR NON-LOCALS (critical for our audience — immigrants who may not know local realities):
  - ALWAYS introduce people by full name + role on first mention: "Pedro Nuno Santos, líder do PS (головна опозиційна партія)"
  - ALWAYS explain Portuguese institutions and acronyms: "AIMA (Agência para a Integração, Migrações e Asilo — міграційна служба)"
  - ALWAYS explain legal/bureaucratic terms: "NIF (Número de Identificação Fiscal — податковий номер, потрібен для будь-яких операцій)"
  - For complex political context, add a brief background as a blockquote: > "Для контексту: PS — соціалісти, були при владі до 2024 року..."
  - Explain WHY something matters for immigrants, not just WHAT happened
  - Compare with Ukrainian realities where helpful: "Junta de Freguesia — це як сільська рада в Україні"
- If this topic CONTINUES or UPDATES a story we already covered, reference the previous article:
  - Mention it in the text: "As we wrote earlier (link)" or "Recall that..."
  - Use the URL format: {{ site_base_url }}/{{'{{'}}previous-slug{{'}}'}}/
  - This builds narrative continuity for readers
</requirements>

